subSubSection.paragraph:
So far reared on five different occasions from the nest bottoms of the Boreal owl (

Aegolius funereus

). Two specimens in the collection of ZMUO have been reared from the nest of the Ural owl (

Strix uralensis

) and one specimen from the nest of the Great tit (

Parus major

). Additionally, three reared specimens of two different rearing events do not state anything about the origin. One specimen has been found in a vacated house. Thirteen specimens in coll. ZMUO and a specimen from the Italian Alps in coll. TLMF have been collected in the wild between 17 June to 21 July, which matches well with the flight time of other 

Monopis

species of these regions.
